                Students Travel to England and Scotland over Spring Break
This spring break, Dr. Peter Thorsheim, assisted by History graduate student Quinn Whittington, led 15 undergraduate and graduate students on an 8-day study abroad program to the United Kingdom. Highlights included visits to the Tower of London, the Cabinet War Rooms, Oxford's Bodleian Library, Bletchley Park, Edinburgh Castle, Arthur's...
